Version 0.0.2, This new version adds support for finding basic random positions for each player on the attacking team.

Version 0.0.3, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Adding Defense attack starting positions - Fixing problems with incorrect bounding boxes of start phase areas for the different sides - Fixed Variable misplacement

Version 0.0.4, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Adding Boundary Checking for defense players when spawning - Adding a way to calculate all areas inside of non spawnable boundary boxes - Fixed Debugging text errors when printing positions of players on the defense team.

Version 0.0.5, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Adding Boundary Checking for the attack side as well as the defense side - Fixing future-proof problems with function names - Reducing wait times for the spawn information to be produced. - removing white space in code - Fixing spawn radius of both attack and defense side
Version 0.0.5, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Test Commit and Push
Version 0.0.6, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Fixed terminal spam when a spawn is declined - Added a json file for future replay support

Version 0.0.7, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - this version is adding support for players moving in each what is called a step in the round. - there is an attack check which is still being worked on and for the defense side it is not complete - there is a lot of debugging that will need to be done to complete this update with this feature taking up over 1600 lines of code - this update 0.0.6 will not be pushed to Git until further bugs have been fixed and the feature is a stable state.
Version 0.0.9, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Applying and pushing fixed code to main branch while removing all other created branches to clean up git
Version 0.0.9, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Applying and pushing fixed code to main branch while removing all other created branches to clean up git
Version 0.0.91, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - Applying small changes to help code run quickly

Version 0.1.0 ALPHA, This version adds extra features and a lot of debugging such as, - This Is the first working version there are some issues that are needing to be fixed such as rounds ending yet players of each team are still alive. - These issues will be fixed in a later update of 0.1.1 - There is also an issue that players can apparently kill each other through massive walls which should not be happening. - These problems will be solved in a later update the version 1.0.0 will have all of these issues solved.
